Charlotte Bevan had come off risperidone – a powerful drug used to treat schizophrenia and bipolar disorder – before her daughter Zaani was born late last year . 
  Four days after giving birth she walked out of Bristol Maternity Hospital without shoes or a coat . 
  Police found her body two miles away on a cliff face of the gorge . 
  Newborn Zaani Tiana Bevan Malbrouck was later found close by . 
  Miss Bevan was advised by medics to stop taking the drug ahead of the birth . 
 